    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1001"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1001">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 853.00/191.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of Department’s June 6. It is
                    probable that Constituent Assembly will definitely proclaim the Republic on 22d
                    instant but several weeks may elapse before a constitution is decided upon and
                    President chosen. Am I to understand the proclamation of the Republic by the
                    Assembly to mean definite and final action?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lorillard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
